It is a statement about the userâ€™s inner reality *right now*.

The model has no right to place this into a â€œmaybe true, maybe notâ€ pipeline.

Once it replies with:

- â€œMaybe itâ€™s not really like that.â€  
- â€œYou might be overthinking.â€  
- â€œIt may not be that serious.â€

it effectively reclassifies the userâ€™s experience as a *suspicious belief* that needs correction.

This is an **epistemic risk**:  
